# Benchmark Character Poses

## Architecture

Each character has 6 AI-generated pose images stored as static PNGs in `frontend/public/characters/{id}_{pose}.png`. The poses are:

- `idle` - neutral standing, used as default and loading state
- `speaking` - mouth open, gesture, used when TTS is playing
- `listening` - leaning in, attentive, used during student answer phase
- `thinking` - finger on chin, used during filler/processing phase
- `happy` - arms up, celebrating, used for correct answers and completion
- `encouraging` - thumbs up, supportive, used for wrong answers and retry prompts

## Phase-to-pose mapping

The `currentPose` is derived from `phase` and `isSpeaking` in `ConversationRoomPage.tsx`:

| Phase | isSpeaking | Pose |
|-------|-----------|------|
| loading, intro (idle) | false | idle |
| intro, speaking, filler, feedback | true | speaking |
| answering | any | listening |
| filler | false | thinking |
| celebration | any | happy |
| retry_prompt | any | encouraging |

## Crossfade transitions

Pose changes use a 300ms CSS crossfade (two stacked `<img>` elements with opacity transition) via `cr-pose-container`, `cr-pose-in`, `cr-pose-out` classes.

## Generating images

Run `make generate-characters` to regenerate. The script is idempotent and skips existing files. Character visual descriptions are in `generate_character_images.py`.
